section.section:
The penalty shall be assessed with consideration given to:
The willfulness of the violation, the extent to which the existence of the violation was known to the violator but uncorrected by the violator, and the extent to which the violator exercised reasonable care;
The extent to which the violation resulted in actual harm to the environment or to human health or safety;
The nature and degree of injury to or interference with general welfare, health, and property;
The extent to which the current violation is part of a recurrent pattern of the same or similar type of violation committed by the violator; and
The extent to which the violation creates the potential for harm to the environment or to human health or safety.
